  "description": "Redevelopment to provide 16 residential units and B1\r\naccommodation with associated landscaping and car parking.\r\nAs shown on drawing nos. P03C; P15B; P16B; P17B; P18B; P19A;\r\nP20A; P21A; and P22A.",
  "decision_conditions": [
    "Condition : 1 - Prior to the commencement of works on site, a scheme\r\n    providing for the insulation of the proposed dwellings\r\n    against the transmission of externally generated traffic\r\n    noise and vibration from the railway line running to the\r\n    north of the site, shall be submitted to and approved by the\r\n    Council. Any works which form part of the scheme shall be\r\n    completed in accordance with the approved details before the\r\n    dwellings are occupied.",
    "Condition : 2 - Detailed drawings, or samples of materials, as appropriate,\r\n    in respect of the following, shall be submitted to and\r\n    approved before the relevant part of the work is begun;\r\n    a) samples of all facing materials;\r\n    b) detail of windows at 1:20 scale.",
    "Condition : 3 - Details of all means of enclosure for all site boundaries\r\n    shall not be other than as have been submitted to and\r\n    approved by the Local Planning Authority before development\r\n    commences on site.",
    "Condition : 4 - A method statement shall be submitted to the Council\r\n    indicating the method of protection of all trees adjoining\r\n    the site. These trees shall be protected to the satisfaction\r\n    of the Local Planning Authority and shall not be damaged or\r\n    destroyed, felled or lopped without the prior written\r\n    consent of the authority.",
    "Condition : 5 - Before development commences a scheme of landscaping shall\r\n    be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning\r\n    Authority. The scheme shall indicate the number, species,\r\n    and heights on planting and position of all new trees/\r\n    plants. The planting shall be carried out in its entirety\r\n    before the end of the first planting season following\r\n    completion of the development. The scheme shall include\r\n    details of the landscaping to the east of the commercial\r\n    building.",
    "Condition : 6 - The car parking shown on approved drawing P03C shall be\r\n    retained for the occupiers of the residential units only.",
    "Condition : 7 - The service area adjacent to the commercial (B1) building\r\n    shall be kept free of parked vehicles and other obstructions\r\n    at all times.",
    "Condition : 8 - Details of the refuse arrangements for the commercial (B1)\r\n    building shall be submitted to and approved by the Local\r\n    Planning Authority before the development commences. These\r\n    details as approved shall be implemented prior to the\r\n    occupation of the building.",
    "Condition : 9 - To ensure that the Council may be satisfied with that the\r\n    development provides an adequate environment within the\r\n    proposed residential units. In accordance with PPG 24,\r\n    policies SHG2, SHG4 land DS6 of the London Borough of Camden\r\n    Unitary Development Plan 2000.",
    "Condition : 10 - To ensure that the Council may be satisfied with the\r\n    external appearance of the building, in accordance with the\r\n    requirements of policies EN1 and EN16 of the London Borough\r\n    of Camden Unitary Development Plan 2000.",
    "Condition : 11 - To ensure that the landscaping is carried out within a\r\n    reasonable period and to maintain a satisfactory standard of\r\n    visual amenity in the scheme, in accordance with the\r\n    requirements of policy EN17 of the London Borough of Camden\r\n    Unitary Development Plan 2000.",
    "Condition : 12 - To ensure the proposed dwellings are adequately insulated\r\n    and to prevent noise and disturbance to future residents.",
    "Condition : 13 - In order to ensure that adequate parking facilities are\r\n    retained for future occupiers.",
    "Condition : 14 - To enable the free flow of service and delivery vehicles to\r\n    the building and to avoid congestion on Kingsford Street.",
    "Condition : 15 - To ensure adequate refuse storage arrangements are made for\r\n    the building.",
    "Condition : 16 - The Council's Engineering Service should be consulted\r\n    regarding the construction of the crossover on the public\r\n    highway and any other work to, under or over the public\r\n    highway, including vaults and thresholds. The Section\r\n    dealing with these matters is located at Camden Town Hall,\r\n    Argyle Street, London WC1H 8EQ, (tel: 020 7278 4444).",
    "Condition : 17 - If a revision to the postal address becomes necessary as a\r\n    result of this development, application under Part 2 of the\r\n    London Building Acts (amendment) Act 1939 should be made to\r\n    Records and Information Team, (Street Naming and Numbering)\r\n    Environment Department, Camden Town Hall, Argyle Street,\r\n    London WC1H 8EQ (tel 020 7974 5613)",
    "Condition : 18 - Your attention is drawn to the fact that there is a separate\r\n    legal agreement with the Council which relates to the\r\n    development for which this permission is granted.",
    "Condition : 19 - The details required pursuant to Additional Condition(s) 1,\r\n    2, 3, 4, 5 and 8 should be submitted with the attached\r\n    approval of details application form together with 5 sets of\r\n    drawings and any other supporting information.",
    "Condition : 20 - With reference to condition 5 the scheme of works should be\r\n    provided to illustrate that the noise criteria included in\r\n    BS8233 are met.",
    "Condition : 21 - To ensure the preservation of the amenity value of the\r\n    tree(s) in question, in accordance with the requirements of\r\n    policy EN81 of the London Borough of Camden Unitary\r\n    Development Plan 2000."
  ],
